From 1b5adbf40334a4648fe9445eb1cdb6b70af57190 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Tetsuya Hayashi <tetsu.h@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 1 Jun 2026 07:15:53 +0900
Subject: [PATCH] prep_redhat_system: limit oneAPI repo to TBB packages

tt-metal only adds the Intel oneAPI repository to get oneTBB 2021+ on
Red Hat family distros. Leaving the repo unrestricted lets DNF satisfy
unrelated packages such as OpenMPI from oneAPI, which can pull older
Intel RPMs signed by keys not advertised by the repository config and
fail package GPG verification.

Restrict the repo to the TBB-related packages required by
intel-oneapi-tbb-devel. This preserves repo_gpgcheck and package
gpgcheck while avoiding accidental dependency resolution through
unrelated oneAPI packages.

Upstream-Status: Pending

Distro-Scope: rocky-9, rocky-10
---
 install_dependencies.sh | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/install_dependencies.sh b/install_dependencies.sh
index 83fe4a3..47241be 100755
--- a/install_dependencies.sh
+++ b/install_dependencies.sh
@@ -308,6 +308,10 @@ enabled=1
 gpgcheck=1
 repo_gpgcheck=1
 gpgkey=https://yum.repos.intel.com/intel-gpg-keys/GPG-PUB-KEY-INTEL-SW-PRODUCTS.PUB
+# Keep the Intel repository scoped to the oneAPI TBB packages tt-metal needs.
+# Without this, DNF may satisfy unrelated dependencies (for example OpenMPI)
+# from oneAPI, pulling older Intel packages signed by keys not listed above.
+includepkgs=intel-oneapi-tbb* intel-oneapi-common-* intel-oneapi-tcm-*
 REPO_EOF
 }
 
